@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(EcCalendar))]

<ComponentApiDoc Type="typeof(EcCalendar)">
    <MainContent>
        <DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
        <Demo Type="typeof(EcCalendar_Demo)" Tabs="false" />

        <DocHeading Title="Dates customization" />
        <p>
            You can change rendering of weekend days by defining your own CSS rule for <code>.weekend</code> class.
            The disabled days get <code>.disabled</code> class.
        </p>
        <p>
            For more detailed customization use the <code>DateCustomizationProvider</code> parameter which allows you setting
            <code>CssClass</code> and <code>Enabled</code> values for every single date rendered.
        </p>

        <DocHeading Id="EcInputDate-EcInputDateRange" Title="EcInputDate, EcInputDateRange" />
        <p>
            <code>EcCalendar</code> is used in implementation of <a href="/components/EcInputDate"><code>EcInputDate</code></a>
            and <a href="/components/EcInputDateRange"><code>EcInputDateRange</code></a> components. See their documentation for more info.
        </p>
    </MainContent>
